Create Project inside github manually and Copy the path Like https://github.com/akhileshkumar4953/MyFile_Notes
Anf then exceute below command to save here from local file
Push Local Files to GitHub

Repository: MyFile_Notes GitHub Repository

Step 1 — Open Project Folder

Open terminal inside your local project folder.

Example:

cd Desktop/MyFile_Notes
Step 2 — Initialize Git
git init

This starts Git in your folder.

Step 3 — Add All Files
git add .

This prepares all files for commit.

Step 4 — Commit Files
git commit -m "First commit"

This saves your code locally.

Step 5 — Connect GitHub Repository
git remote add origin https://github.com/akhileshkumar4953/MyFile_Notes.git

This connects local folder to GitHub repository.

Step 6 — Push Files to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
